messages.text: You look great in that red dress.
Who is this?
Just someone who appreciate beauty.
LOL. You’re cute. You have a name.
We all have names. Or so I’m told Lyn.
You going to give me yours?
You can call me SA.
You like wrapping yourself up in mystery?
Are you into that kind of thing?
Depends I guess.
Where do I know you from?
Around.
Like where?
From school.
I saw you at your part time job too.
You look really cute in your Candy Striper
You saw me at the hospital?
And the mall.
And the pool.
Wait. I went to the pool after hours. Only a handful of people came with us.
Adam is this you? You got a new phone or something?
I’m not Adam. Don’t compare me to that idiot.
Then who are you?
Someone who loves you Lyn.
Someone who would do anything for you.
Just like that Bruno Mars song. I’ll die for you Lyn.
That’s just weird. How did you even get my number?
I have my ways of getting the things I want.
I want you Lyn. I’ve wanted you since fifth grade. But you never notice me.
Why? What do idiots like Adam have that I don’t? Why do you look through me?
Why won’t you just admit that I’m the kind of boy you really want?
I don’t even know who you are.
But you told Mary you were done with boys like Adam.
Boys who only had sex on their minds.
You told her that you wanted someone who would hold the door for you.
Someone who would treat you like the princess that you are.
How do you know that?
Seriously who is this?
I said that over the phone. I was in my room. You can’t know that at all.
I know everything about you Lyn.
You don’t have to close your blinds I’m not outside.
WTF! Where are you? Who are you?
I’m trying to confess my feelings for you Lyn.
Accept me. Accept my love for you.
No! Stop texting me.
I have to text you. I don’t think I’m brave enough to call yet.
Don’t you dare call me you weirdo.
Don’t do that Lyn. Don’t be like the others.
Don’t be the mean girl they all think you are. Why do you do this to yourself?
Why do you hang out with people who mean nothing to you?
Who treat you worse than dirt? I would never hurt you Lyn. I love you.
What do you know about?
I know that your friend Mary is the one that started the rumors about you.
What? No way. Mary would never do that.
Of course she would. Because she wanted Adam and you had him.
I know that Adam was sleeping around behind your back.
I know you pretend to be one of them but you’re hard working.
You study to stay at the top of the class.
You want to be popular but you won’t let your grades fall for it.
I know that you lied about being sick just so you didn’t have to go to Brad party.
You stayed home and watched Frozen with your little sister.
How? How can you know these things.
Because this is how deep my love flows for you.
There is nothing that I wouldn’t do for you.
There is nothing that I alone don’t know about you.
Why me? What do you want with me? What did I do to earn your love?
Your kindness touched me. It melted my frozen heart.
Your kindness made me see the beauty in the world.
You brought me out of my darkness. I love you Lyn.
I fell in love with you the day you smiled at me.
But I don’t even know who you are.
You don’t need to know me yet.
At least tell me something about yourself.
You know the important things about me. That I love you.
That I would do anything for you.
What does that mean?
It means what I say. I would do anything for you Lyn. I would die for you.
I would kill for you.
Why would I want you to do any of those things.
I know. I know how much you hate your stepfather. I know the ways he hurt you.
Stop it! You don’t know anything.
I know it’s hard to talk about. But I can remove the pain in your life.
If you love me back. I would do anything for you Lyn.
Your enemies would become my enemies. Your pain is my pain.
Your heart...is my heart.
You sound crazy. Stop texting me.
I can’t. I’ve finally built up the courage to text you.
I feel as if I’m going to explode with excitement.
Lyn, my Lyn having a conversation with me.
I never thought this day would come. You should smile some more Lyn.
This is a big day for us. Don’t frown so much when we’re talking.
I want you to be as happy as I am.
How can you see me? Are you in my house?
I wish I had that kind of courage. To stand where you are.
To enter the place that you eat...sleep...bathe. I wish.
If you’re stalking me it’s against the law.
You’d be surprised how lacks the stalking laws are in this country.
What do you want from me?
To start our romance. For you to fall in love with me.
For you to be indebted to me. For you to trust and reply on me.
Then what? I don’t even know you. How can I love you if I don’t know you.
I want to prove my love to you first. I’m not a brave man.
I want to lay my gift at your feet because I tell you the things about me.
I know I’m not as...impressive as you.
If I want your love I must earn it first.
Fine, you want me to love you.
It is the only thing I want in this world.
For you to look at me. To see me. To love me.
Then do it. I’ll love you if you get rid of my stepfather.
I knew you would say that. You need only look in garage for that gift.
Stop screaming Lyn. You wanted this.
Say it. Say the words I want to hear. Give me my reward for a job well done.
They’ll . . .
Find him in his car in the garage and think he killed himself.
The letter confessing to his sins. Sins that he can no longer bare.
Sins of hurting his beautiful step-daughter.
I...You?
Say it Lyn. Don’t make me wait.
I...I love you, SA.
